The most important design rule

If I had to compress the whole plan into one principle, it would be:

Generate truth dynamically, but freeze it before evaluation.

That gives you:

flexibility for unknown use cases
fairness across model comparisons
reproducibility across runs
a much stronger QuickStart story
Final framing you can use internally

Your QuickStart can be positioned as:

A harness-style evaluation framework for regulated RAG systems, where each run captures the question, structured truth, retrieved evidence, model outputs, and multi-layer scoring to assess retrieval quality, answer quality, and compliance-grounded correctness.


Should the comparison be stored?
I would say:
Yes, but lightly.
You should definitely store:


per-run metadata


truth


each model’s output


each model’s scores


For the final comparison result, you have two options:
Option 1 — Recompute comparison from stored runs
Store only:


run


truth


model outputs


model scores


Then compute the comparison whenever needed.
This is good if:


comparison rules may evolve


you want to avoid stale stored winner results


Option 2 — Store comparison snapshot too
Also save:


winner


loser


tie/fail status


comparison summary


comparison timestamp


comparison rules version


This is good if:


you want historical auditability


you want to know what the system concluded at that time


My recommendation
Store both:


the underlying artifacts as source of truth


a lightweight comparison snapshot as derived output


That way:


you can show historical results quickly


you can always re-run comparison later if rules change



Best structure
I’d think about it like this:
Stored permanently


run.json


truth.json


model_a_output.json


model_b_output.json


model_a_score.json


model_b_score.json


Optional derived artifact


comparison.json


Where comparison.json contains something like:


run id


model A id


model B id


winner


comparison summary


rule/version used to compare


whether comparison is current or recomputed



Should comparison always be re-runnable?
Yes.
That is important.
Because if you later change:


weights


thresholds


gates


profile logic


you may want to re-run the comparison without re-running generation itself.
So the architecture should allow:
Re-run comparison only
using saved:


truth


outputs


scores


And maybe also:
Re-run scoring + comparison
if scoring logic changed
And separately:
Re-run full evaluation
if retrieval/model/prompt changed
That gives you flexibility.

Clean mental model
Think of it in layers:
Layer 1 — Truth
What should be true for this question
Layer 2 — Model runs
What each model retrieved and answered
Layer 3 — Per-model scoring
How well each model did on its own
Layer 4 — Comparison
Which one did better, if either is acceptable
That last layer should be derived from the first three.

Short answer


Deterministic checks are added by your evaluation backend


They should be driven by the profile/business rules, not invented by AI


Comparison still fits at the end of the pipeline


It should compare the saved per-model results


Yes, comparison can be stored, but as a derived artifact


The important thing is that it should also be re-runnable from saved run artifacts


